Hi there

Andree Valle-Campos (l/he/his)

Im a geneticist skilled in health data science

I take data problems to learn new tools in the route to solve them, motivated by causal questions and reproducible research.

Continuously integrating open science, software development and teaching online better practices!

Interested in quantitative and systems developmental biology, bioengineering approaches, and configuration principles.

This site contains links to all my (reusable) scientific contributions. Here is a structured pdf version of my cv/resume in english.

cv

  • I have my list of academic publications in orcid and scholar;
  • I did my MSc research about human mobility and malaria history in the peruvian amazon (UPCH, 2018);
  • I did my BSc research about antibody responses and severe vivax malaria with protein microarrays (UNMSM, 2015);

also

  • I am a fluent R programmer, proficient data wrangler and visualization enthusiast.
